New Records: Jayson Tatum nearly achieved a triple-double with 24 points, 11 rebounds, and 9 assists.
RJ Barrett recorded his first career triple-double with 25 points, 10 rebounds, and 15 assists.
Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum hit a game-winning three-pointer at the buzzer to send the game into overtime.
The game went into overtime after Jaylen Brown tied the game with a three-pointer.
RJ Barrett became the first Canadian to score 25 points, 10 rebounds, and 15 assists in a single game.
Pre-Game Insights: The Celtics were well-rested after their last game against the Brooklyn Nets.
The Raptors played the second game of a back-to-back after losing to the Detroit Pistons the previous night.
Post-Match Reflections: Jayson Tatum expressed confidence in his ability to make the game-winning shot.
The Celtics' victory was seen as a crucial step toward their championship aspirations.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Celtics set a season-high 21 three-pointers made in the game.
The Raptors' performance was overshadowed by their inability to win on the road against a top-tier opponent.
Others: The game was the second meeting between the two teams in November 2024.
